Happy Monday, friends. I feel like I haven’t truly introduced myself on here in a hot minute. I’m Hailey & I’ve been behind the chair about 14 years now. Last Valentine’s Day, I officially opened my salon @saltandlighthair and it’s been the best. I have a husband and a 3 year old named Arrow that I’m quite literally obsessed with. But my first love is Jesus. 🤍 I have an unhealthy addiction to The Office. Most of my clients can just assume it will be on in my suite at the salon. I truly love what I do and getting the privilege of making people feel more beautiful than they already are. My goal is to always make you feel at home & safe in my chair.

If you read this far, leave a comment with your fav character from The Office. 👀

Why massage your scalp? It improves circulation in the scalp which will nourish those hair roots which then triggers ✨growth✨
For many (*raises hand*), 2023 has been tough. The stressful moments always tend to make themselves known with hair loss. The tension our scalps hold in those stressful life moments causes the blockage of adequate blood flow to our hair follicles.
A scalp massage (especially using my fav rosemary oil) helps relax the hair follicles. It obviously feels amazing AND it creates more blood circulation to the root which again.. triggers GROWTH! ✨

#hairgrowthtips #healthyhairtips #scalpmassage

2024 is our year to take care of ourselves. Physically, spirtually and mentally.
